# Phase 22A audit hardening (security advisor F4):
# Any change to deploy workflows or Azure infra requires CODEOWNERS
# (operator) approval before merge. With branch protection set to
# "Require review from Code Owners", this means a malicious PR landing
# on main can't carry workflow / Bicep changes through silently.
#
# Solo-operator caveat: this is informational only without a branch
# protection rule that requires codeowner review. Set up via:
#   gh api -X PUT repos/msrivas-7/CodeTutor-AI/branches/main/protection
# with `required_pull_request_reviews.require_code_owner_reviews=true`.
# For a solo product, the value is the audit trail + the explicit
# "second look" pause before merging high-blast-radius changes.

# Deploy workflows + GitHub Actions definitions
/.github/workflows/      @msrivas-7
/.github/CODEOWNERS      @msrivas-7

# Azure Bicep infrastructure
/infra/azure/            @msrivas-7

# Backend boot path + service-role-touching modules
/backend/src/index.ts    @msrivas-7
/backend/src/config.ts   @msrivas-7
